MINISTER of Public Works Patricia de Lille’s husband has died. The minister’s family made the announcement in a statement. Edwin de Lille died on Sunday evening after a long illness. His death comes a year before their 50th wedding anniversary. Minister De Lille said her husband was a loving father to their only son, Alistair, and a supportive husband. She said he supported her throughout her political career and gave her the freedom to fully pursue her work in serving the country. “Our marriage was built on respect. Eddie was a true partner in the sense of the word and never stopped me from following my convictions. There was respect and support until his final days,” she said.